[231.65108, "o", "\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[231.657519, "o", "/usr/bin/mysql_secure_installation: Deprecated program name. It will be removed in a future release, use 'mariadb-secure-installation' instead\r\n"]
[231.665073, "o", "\r\nNOTE: MariaDB is secure by default. Running this script is mostly\r\n      unecessary and it will likely be removed in a future release,\r\n      but it is for now preserved for backwards compatibility.\r\n\r\nEnter root user password or leave blank:\r\n\r\n"]
[231.671262, "o", "Enter current password for root (enter for none): "]
[234.31781, "o", "\r\n"]
[234.407774, "o", "OK, successfully used password, moving on...\r\n\r\nSetting the root password or using the unix_socket ensures that nobody\r\ncan log into the MariaDB root user without the proper authorisation.\r\n\r\nYou already have your root account protected, so you can safely answer 'n'.\r\n\r\n"]
[234.407839, "o", "Switch to unix_socket authentication [Y/n] "]
[238.934166, "o", "n"]
[239.634304, "o", "\r\n"]
[239.634836, "o", " ... skipping.\r\n\r\n"]
[239.635273, "o", "You already have your root account protected, so you can safely answer 'n'.\r\n\r\nChange the root password? [Y/n] "]
[241.201581, "o", "r"]
[241.349679, "o", "a"]
[241.699612, "o", "n"]
[241.967553, "o", "g"]
[242.234242, "o", "\b \b"]
[242.484319, "o", "\b \b"]
[242.517446, "o", "\b \b"]
[242.550821, "o", "\b \b"]
[246.733741, "o", "y"]
[247.211608, "o", "\r\n"]
[247.215617, "o", "New password: "]
[249.767852, "o", "\r\nRe-enter new password: "]
[252.21763, "o", "\r\n"]
[252.334027, "o", "Password updated successfully!\r\nReloading privilege tables..\r\n"]
[252.372424, "o", " ... Success!\r\n\r\n"]
[252.376345, "o", "\r\nBy default, a MariaDB installation has an anonymous user, allowing anyone\r\nto log into MariaDB without having to have a user account created for\r\nthem.  This is intended only for testing, and to make the installation\r\ngo a bit smoother.  You should remove them before moving into a\r\nproduction environment.\r\n\r\n"]
[252.376408, "o", "Remove anonymous users? [Y/n] "]
[256.451066, "o", "y"]
[256.851071, "o", "\r\n"]
[256.916438, "o", "Query OK, 2 rows affected\r\n"]
[256.916936, "o", "SQL executed without errors!\r\n\r\n"]
[256.917133, "o", "Normally, root should only be allowed to connect from 'localhost'.  This\r\nensures that someone cannot guess at the root password from the network.\r\n\r\nDisallow root login remotely? [Y/n] "]
[258.201049, "o", "y"]
[258.784229, "o", "\r\n"]
[258.820133, "o", "Query OK, 0 rows affected\r\n"]
[258.820355, "o", "SQL executed without errors!\r\n\r\nBy default, MariaDB comes with a database named 'test' that anyone can\r\naccess.  This is also intended only for testing, and should be removed\r\nbefore moving into a production environment.\r\n"]
[258.820537, "o", "\r\nRemove test database and access to it? [Y/n] "]
[259.951018, "o", "y"]
[260.651068, "o", "\r\n"]
[260.651648, "o", " - Dropping test database...\r\n"]
[260.693057, "o", "Query OK, 0 rows affected\r\n"]
[260.694061, "o", "SQL executed without errors!\r\n - Removing privileges on test database...\r\n"]
[260.726272, "o", "Query OK, 2 rows affected\r\n"]
[260.726528, "o", "SQL executed without errors!\r\n\r\nReloading the privilege tables will ensure that all changes made so far\r\nwill take effect immediately.\r\n"]
[260.726655, "o", "\r\nReload privilege tables now? [Y/n] "]
[261.611739, "o", "y"]
[264.810933, "o", "\r\n"]
[264.844087, "o", " ... Success!\r\n\r\nCleaning up...\r\n"]
[264.845555, "o", "\r\nAll done!  If you've completed all of the above steps, your MariaDB\r\ninstallation should now be secure.\r\n\r\nThanks for using MariaDB!\r\n"]
[264.846002, "o", "\u001b[?2004h[root@project project]# "]
