[1595.776969, "o", "\u001b[H; PHP output character encoding is set to empty.\r\n; If empty, default_charset is used.\u001b[3;3HSee also output_buffer.\u001b[53X\u001b[4;3Hhttps://php.net/output-encoding\u001b[43X\u001b[5;2Houtput_encoding =\u001b[52X\r\n\u001b[71X\u001b[7;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[15X\u001b[8;2H Paths and Directories ;    \r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\r\n\u001b[77X\u001b[11;3HUNIX: \"/path1:/path2\"\u001b[54X\u001b[12;2Hinclude_path = \".:/php/includes\"\u001b[29X\u001b[13;2H\u001b[68X\u001b[14;3HWindows: \"\\path1;\\path2\"\u001b[51X\u001b[15;2Hinclude_path = \".;c:\\php\\includes\"\r\n;\u001b[23X\r\n; PHP's default setting for include_path is \".;/path/to/php/pear\"\u001b[18;3Hhttps://php.net/include-path\u001b[45X\r\n\u001b[72X\u001b[20;3HThe root of the PHP pages, used only if nonempty\u001b[21;3Hif PHP was not compiled with FORCE_REDIRECT, you SHOULD set doc_root\u001b[22;3Hif you are running php as a CGI under any web server (other than IIS)\u001b[23;2H see documentation for security issues.  The alternate is to use the\r\n; cgi.force_redirect configuration below\u001b[25;3Hhttps://php.net/doc-root\u001b[31X\r\ndoc_root =\u001b[45X\r\n\u001b[35X\n; The directory under which PHP opens the script using /~username used only\r\n; if nonempty.\u001b[30;3Hhttps://php.net/user-dir\u001b[43X\r\nuser_dir =\u001b[33X\r\n\u001b[37X\u001b[33;2H Directory in which the loadable \u001b[30m\u001b[103mextensions\u001b[m\u000f (modules) reside.\u001b[34;2H https://php.net/extension-dir\r\nextension_dir =\u001b[92m \"/usr/lib/php/modules/\"\u001b[36;2H\u001b[m\u000f On windows:\u001b[15X\u001b[37;2Hextension_dir = \"ext\"\u001b[6X\u001b[39;3HDirectory where the temporary files should be placed.\u001b[22X\u001b[40;3HDefaults to the system default (see sys_get_temp_dir)\u001b[25X\u001b[41;2Hsys_temp_dir = \"/tmp\"\u001b[57X\r\n\u001b[29X\u001b[43;3HWhether or not to enable the dl() function.  The dl() function does NOT work\u001b[44;2H properly in multithreaded servers, such as IIS or Zeus, and is automatically\r\n; disabled on them.\u001b[46;3Hhttps://php.net/enable-dl\u001b[53X\r\nenable_dl =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[64X\r\n\u001b[32X\u001b[49;3Hcgi.force_redirect is necessary to provide security running PHP as a CGI under\u001b[50;3Hmost web servers.  Left undefined, PHP turns this on by default.  You can\u001b[51;2H turn it off here AT YOUR OWN RISK\r\n; **You CAN safely turn this off for IIS, in fact, you MUST.**\u001b[53;3Hhttps://php.net/cgi.force-redirect\u001b[46X\u001b[54;2Hcgi.force_redirect = 1\u001b[62X\r\n\u001b[8X\u001b[56;3Hif cgi.nph is enabled it will force cgi to always sent Status: 200 with\u001b[57;2H every request. PHP's default behavior is to disable this feature.\r\n;cgi.nph = 1\r\n\u001b[55X\u001b[60;3Hif cgi.force_redirect is turned on, and you are not running under Apache or Netscape\r\n; (iPlanet) web servers, you MAY need to set an environment variable name that PHP\r\n; will look for to know it is OK to continue execution.  Setting this variable MAY\u001b[63;3Hcause security issues, KNOW WHAT YOU ARE DOING FIRST.\u001b[21X\u001b[64;3Hhttps://php.net/cgi.redirect-status-env\u001b[32X\u001b[65;2Hcgi.redirect_status_env =\u001b[44X\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f756,35         39\u001b[67;12H\u001b[?25h"]
[1596.538461, "o", "\u001b[?25l\b\u001b[m\u000f \b"]
[1596.542931, "o", "\u001b[Hunserialize_callback_func =\u001b[21X\r\n\u001b[36X\u001b[3;3HThe unserialize_max_depth specifies the default depth limit for unserialized\u001b[4;3Hstructures. Setting the depth limit too high may result in stack overflows\u001b[5;2H during unserialization. The unserialize_max_depth ini setting can be\r\n; overridden by the max_depth option on individual unserialize() calls.\u001b[7;2H A value of 0 disables the depth limit.\u001b[8;2Hunserialize_max_depth = 4096\r\n\u001b[25X\n; When floats & doubles are serialized, store serialize_precision significant\u001b[11;3Hdigits after the floating point. The default value ensures that when floats\u001b[12;2H are decoded with unserialize, the data will remain the same.\u001b[13;2H The value is also used for json_encode when encoding double values.\u001b[14;3HIf -1 is used, then dtoa mode 0 is used which automatically select the best\u001b[15;2H precision.\u001b[23X\r\nserialize_precision =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[65X\u001b[18;3Hopen_basedir, if set, limits all file operations to the defined directory\r\n; and below.  This directive makes most sense if used in a per-directory\u001b[20;3Hor per-virtualhost web server configuration file\u001b[21;3HNote: disables the realpath cache\u001b[35X\u001b[22;3Hhttps://php.net/open-basedir\u001b[41X\u001b[23;2Hopen_basedir =\u001b[54X\r\n\u001b[40X\u001b[25;3HThis directive allows you to disable certain functions.\r\n; It receives a comma-delimited list of function names.\r\n; https://php.net/disable-functions\r\ndisable_functions =\u001b[56X\r\n\u001b[14X\u001b[30;3HColors for Syntax Highlighting mode.  Anything that's acceptable in\r\n; <span style=\"color: ???????\"> would work.\r\n; https://php.net/syntax-highlighting\u001b[33;2Hhighlight.string  = #DD0000\u001b[34X\u001b[34;2Hhighlight.comment = #FF9900   \r\n;highlight.keyword = #007700\u001b[11X\u001b[36;2Hhighlight.default = #0000BB\u001b[37;2Hhighlight.html    = #000000\u001b[39;3HIf enabled, the request will be allowed to complete even if the user aborts\u001b[40;3Hthe request. Consider enabling it if executing long requests, which may end up\u001b[41;2H being interrupted by the user or a browser timing out. PHP's default behavior\r\n; is to disable this feature.\u001b[43;3Hhttps://php.net/ignore-user-abort\u001b[43X\u001b[44;2Hignore_user_abort = On\u001b[55X\r\n\u001b[19X\u001b[46;3HDetermines the size of the realpath cache to be used by PHP. This value should\r\n; be increased on systems where PHP opens many files to reflect the quantity of\r\n; the file operations performed.\u001b[49;3HNote: if open_basedir is set, the cache is disabled\u001b[27X\u001b[50;3Hhttps://php.net/realpath-cache-size\u001b[38X\u001b[51;2Hrealpath_cache_size = 4096k\u001b[7X\r\n\u001b[62X\u001b[53;3HDuration of time, in seconds for which to cache realpath information for a given\u001b[54;2H file or directory. For systems with rarely changing files, consider increasing this\r\n; value.\u001b[56;3Hhttps://php.net/realpath-cache-ttl\u001b[37X\u001b[57;2Hrealpath_cache_ttl = 120\u001b[42X\r\n\u001b[12X\n; Enables or disables the circular reference collector.\u001b[60;3Hhttps://php.net/zend.enable-gc\u001b[54X\r\nzend.enable_gc =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[63X\r\n\u001b[82X\u001b[63;3HIf enabled, scripts may be written in encodings that are incompatible with\u001b[64;3Hthe scanner.  CP936, Big5, CP949 and Shift_JIS are the examples of such\u001b[65;2H encodings.  To use this feature, mbstring \u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension\u001b[m\u000f must be enabled.\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f360,45         16\u001b[67;11H\u001b[?25h"]
[1596.988551, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[m\u000f="]
[1596.993155, "o", "\u001b[H; Whether to allow include/require to open URLs (like https:// or ftp://) as files.\r\n; https://php.net/allow-url-include\r\nallow_url_include =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[55X\r\n\u001b[76X\u001b[5;3HDefine the anonymous ftp password (your email address). PHP's default setting\u001b[6;3Hfor this is empty.\u001b[51X\u001b[7;3Hhttps://php.net/from\u001b[18X\u001b[8;2Hfrom=\"john@doe.com\"\u001b[9X\u001b[10;3HDefine the User-Agent string. PHP's default setting for this is empty.\u001b[5X\u001b[11;3Hhttps://php.net/user-agent\u001b[49X\u001b[12;2Huser_agent=\"PHP\"\u001b[45X\r\n\u001b[69X\u001b[14;3HDefault timeout for socket based streams (seconds)\u001b[25X\u001b[15;3Hhttps://php.net/default-socket-timeout\r\ndefault_socket_timeout = 60\u001b[18;3HIf your scripts have to deal with files from Macintosh systems,\u001b[10X\u001b[19;3Hor you are running on a Mac and need to deal with files from\u001b[10X\u001b[20;3Hunix or win32 systems, setting this flag will cause PHP to\u001b[21;3Hautomatically detect the EOL character in those files so that\u001b[22;3Hfgets() and file() will work regardless of the source of the file.\u001b[23;2H https://php.net/auto-detect-line-endings\r\n;auto_detect_line_endings = Off\r\n\u001b[57X\u001b[26;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[33X\u001b[27;3HDynamic Extensions ;\u001b[13X\r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[30;3HIf you wish to have an extension loaded automatically, use the following\u001b[31;3Hsyntax:\u001b[34X\u001b[32;2H\u001b[36X\n   \u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fmodulename    \u001b[34;2H\u001b[27X\n For example:\u001b[14X\u001b[36;2H\u001b[27X\n   \u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fmysqli\u001b[8X\r\n;\u001b[39;3HWhen the extension library to load is not located in the default extension \u001b[40;3Hdirectory, You may specify an absolute path to the library file:\u001b[14X\u001b[41;2H\u001b[78X\u001b[42;3H  \u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000f/path/to/extension/mysqli.so\u001b[43;2H\u001b[34X\n Note : The syntax used in previous PHP versions ('\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000f<ext>.so' and\r\n; '\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000f'php_<ext>.dll') is supported for legacy reasons and may be\u001b[46;3Hdeprecated in a future PHP major version. So, when it is possible, please\u001b[5X\u001b[47;3Hmove to the new ('\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000f<ext>) syntax.\u001b[35X\u001b[48;2H\u001b[31X\n\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fbcmath\u001b[36X\u001b[50;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fbz2\u001b[23X\u001b[51;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fcalendar\u001b[9X\r\n\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[92mcurl\u001b[53;2H\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fdba\u001b[68X\u001b[54;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fenchant\u001b[67X\u001b[55;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fexif\u001b[56;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fffi\u001b[22X\u001b[57;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fftp\u001b[11X\r\n\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[92mgd\u001b[59;2H\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fgettext\u001b[37X\u001b[60;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fgmp\u001b[18X\r\n;\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000ficonv   \r\n\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[92mintl\u001b[63;2H\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fldap\u001b[61X\r\n\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[92mmysqli\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[57X\u001b[65;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fodbc\u001b[55X\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f896,5          47\u001b[67;12H\u001b[?25h"]
[1601.192748, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[m\u000f\r\u001b[67;1H\u001b[11X\u001b[1;3HSo only set this entry, if you really want to implement such a\u001b[19X\u001b[2;3Hcallback-function.\u001b[15X\r\nunserialize_callback_func =\u001b[5;3HThe unserialize_max_depth specifies the default depth limit for unserialized \u001b[6;3Hstructures. Setting the depth limit too high may result in stack overflows\u001b[7;3Hduring unserialization. The unserialize_max_depth ini setting can be\u001b[8;2H overridden by the max_depth option on individual unserialize() calls.\r\n; A value of 0 disables the depth limit.\u001b[10;2Hunserialize_max_depth = 4096\u001b[43X\r\n\u001b[28X\u001b[12;2H When floats & doubles are serialized, store serialize_precision significant\r\n; digits after the floating point. The default value ensures that when floats\u001b[14;3Hare decoded with unserialize, the data will remain the same.\u001b[15;3HThe value is also used for json_encode when encoding double values.\r\n; If -1 is used, then dtoa mode 0 is used which automatically select the best\r\n; precision.\r\nserialize_precision =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[41X\r\n\u001b[62X\u001b[20;3Hopen_basedir, if set, limits all file operations to the defined directory\u001b[21;4Hnd below.  This directive makes most sense if used in a per-directory\u001b[22;3Hor per-virtualhost web server configuration file.\u001b[17X\u001b[23;3HNote: disables the realpath cache\u001b[7X\u001b[24;2H https://php.net/open-basedir \r\n;open_basedir =\r\n\u001b[22X\u001b[27;3HThis directive allows you to disable certain functions.\u001b[28;2H It receives a comma-delimited list of function names.\r\n; https://php.net/disable-functions\r\ndisable_functions =\u001b[55X\r\n\u001b[9X\u001b[32;2H Colors for Syntax Highlighting mode.  Anything that's acceptable in\u001b[33;3H<span style=\"color: ???????\"> would work.\u001b[34;2H https://php.net/syntax-highlighting\u001b[35;2Hhighlight.string  = #DD0000\u001b[36;2Hhighlight.comment = #FF9900\u001b[37;2Hhighlight.keyword = #007700\u001b[38;2Hhighlight.default = #0000BB\u001b[39;2Hhighlight.html    = #000000\u001b[48X\r\n\u001b[66X\u001b[41;2H If enabled, the request will be allowed to complete even if the user aborts\u001b[42;3Hthe request. Consider enabling it if executing long requests, which may end up\u001b[43;2H being interrupted by the user or a browser timing out. PHP's default behavior\u001b[44;3His to disable this feature.\u001b[46X\u001b[45;3Hhttps://php.net/ignore-user-abort\u001b[37X\u001b[46;2Hignore_user_abort = On\u001b[52X\r\n\u001b[44X\u001b[48;2H Determines the size of the realpath cache to be used by PHP. This value should\u001b[49;2H be increased on systems where PHP opens many files to reflect the quantity of\u001b[50;2H the file operations performed.\u001b[51;2H Note: if open_basedir is set, the cache is disabled\r\n; https://php.net/realpath-cache-size\u001b[53;2Hrealpath_cache_size = 4096k\r\n\u001b[18X\u001b[55;2H Duration of time, in seconds for which to cache realpath information for a given\u001b[56;2H file or directory. For systems with rarely changing files, consider increasing this\u001b[57;2H value.\u001b[6X\r\n; https://php.net/realpath-cache-ttl\u001b[59;2Hrealpath_cache_ttl = 120\r\n\u001b[14X\u001b[61;2H Enables or disables the circular reference collector.\r\n; https://php.net/zend.enable-gc\r\nzend.enable_gc =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[16X\u001b[65;2H If enabled, scripts may be written in encodings that are incompatible with\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f358,1          16\u001b[?112c\u001b[?1002h\u001b[?1006h\r\u001b[A\u001b[?25h"]
